FMD news: New Zealand -- FMD risk to exports (follow-up)
---------------------
Summary: A letter sent to the Prime Minister claims FMD has already been
released on Waiheke Island. It sought money and a change in the country's
tax policies, and threatened another release of the disease elsewhere this
week. An investigation has been launched and biosecurity director Barry
O'Neil says major trading partners are being informed. He says exotic
disease staff have placed a restricted area notice on the island where
there are 18 000 sheep and 2500 cattle. It could be weeks before Waiheke
Island knows whether it is clear of FMD, as the animals will be tested
every 48 hours until disease can be ruled out, which may be 2 weeks. He
says they are also tracing all livestock and risk material that has left
the island in the past 24 hours. Farmers are being warned not to panic over
the bioterrorism claim.
Full text:
<http://home.nzcity.co.nz/news/default.asp?id=50424&c=w>
<http://www.nzherald.co.nz/index.cfm?c_id=1&ObjectID=10124890>
<http://www.newstalkzb.co.nz/newsdetail1.asp?storyID=72448>
