FMD News: New Zealand -- farmers left in the dark over FMD threat (follow-up)
---------------------
Summary: Waiheke farmers were left in the dark about the FMD scare,
learning about the possible threat to their livestock from news reports.
Their reactions were low-key as they waited for more information. At
Waiheke Station, Neville Dick was waiting for some kind of official word.
"I've had a few calls from journalists, but haven't heard from MAF." "Some
people get off on the thought that there'll be a panic, just to scare the
locals. I'm 95 per cent certain it will be a hoax," said Mr Walker, who has
lived on the island for 30 years. Another farm owner was also sure it would
be a hoax. "Ridiculous, it's a lot of nonsense." Waiheke veterinarian John
Hewitt said no one had reported sick animals.
Full text: <http://www.stuff.co.nz/stuff/0,2106,3276084a7693,00.html>
